> This chilli is a firm favourite of our chef Mimi. It is inspired by Mimi's veggie
> friend Emily who whipped this up one night and having originally turned her nose
> up at lentils, Mimi proceeded to devour three portions. It is packed with a
> whole array of delicious ingredients and we hope you enjoy this taste sensation
> as much as we do!

Pre-heat the #oven{} to 180 degrees. Peel and finely chop the @red onion{1}. Remove
the core from the @red pepper{1} and chop into (roughly) 2cm squares.

Heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a #non-stick frying pan{} on low heat and cook the onion
for ~{3%minutes} until it softens. Put the pepper chunks into the #frying pan{}
with the onion, turn the heat to medium and cook for ~{3%minutes}. Next add the
@cumin{1/2%tsp}, @ground coriander{1/2%tsp}, @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, a pinch of
@chilli flakes{1/4%tsp} (depending on how spicy you like it!) and a pinch of
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Stir together and cook for another ~{1%minute}.

Meanwhile, boil @water{350%ml} in a #pot{} with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Once boiling, add
your @basmati rice{1} to the pot and turn the heat to low. Cover the pot with a
#lid{} and leave on a low heat for ~{10%minutes}. After ~{10%minutes} remove
from the heat and leave to rest for ~{10%minutes}. Don't peek under the lid
until the 20 mins are up!

Add the @red split lentils{3%tbsp} to the onions as well as the
@chopped tomatoes{1%400g can} and @water{150%ml}. Stir together and let the
mixture bubble away on low heat uncovered for ~{15%minutes} until it is a lovely
thick consistency. After ~{5%minutes}, drain and rinse the @butter beans{1/2%400g can}
and add them to the pan together with another pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch} if needed.

> Tip: Stir occasionally to make sure the lentils aren't sticking to the bottom
> of the pan.

While the chilli and rice are cooking cut the @courgette{3/4} in half lengthways,
chop each half into four lengths and then into 6cm sticks. Toss the courgettes in
@olive oil{1%tbsp}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and some @pepper{}. Roast in the oven for
~{15%minutes}.

Time for the guacamole! Slice lengthways into the @avocado{1}, once you reach the
stone turn the avocado around to cut it in half. Twist each half and pull it apart
then scoop out all of the insides into a #bowl{}. Add the juice of @lime{1/2}(juiced)
and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Mash it with a #fork{} until you
have a slightly lumpy guacamole.

Once the rice is cooked, chop the @coriander{3}(chopped), add to the rice and stir.
The courgettes should now be cooked and the chilli thick and tomatoey. Serve the
rice with your lentil chilli, a dollop of guacamole and some courgettes. Done!